comments.body:
Thanks, @kelynch ! ok. Reading through the embargo types and expectations on that page,  I see a few things in the document you shared that seem contradictory to above (and I just want to make sure I understand correctly). 

- _To enhance the reach and utility of this resource, the [library created a digital archive in 2014 (http://undergraduateresearch.princeton.edu/feature-article/senior-thesis-archive-goes-digital)to enable members of the Princeton University community (our students, faculty, staff) and other authorized users of our computing network to access copies of senior theses online.) :_ This does not sound like Open. This sounds like Princeton University Net ID or getting access to view something via Special Collections?
- Online Access: _accessible online to authorized users of the Princeton University computing network (as described above)._ again, this sounds like Princeton Net ID/access via Special Collections.
- Walk-in Access Only: as you note above. If they want their desktop to hang with Figgy, we had to have Steph A. and her team come in to help with that as well for Special Collections. Has Steph been over there to see what the setup is like? 
Am I reading this correctly?
Here are the Mudd workstation IPs that can access walk-in theses - https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/princeton-5/blob/dataspace-prod/dspace/config/modules/authentication-ip.cfg#L313

> Thanks, @kelynch ! ok. Reading through the embargo types and expectations on that page, I see a few things in the document you shared that seem contradictory to above (and I just want to make sure I understand correctly).

Thanks @kelea99!  To try to answer your questions in order:

> To enhance the reach and utility of this resource, the [library created a digital archive in 2014 (http://undergraduateresearch.princeton.edu/feature-article/senior-thesis-archive-goes-digital)to enable members of the Princeton University community (our students, faculty, staff) and other authorized users of our computing network to access copies of senior theses online.) : This does not sound like Open. This sounds like Princeton University Net ID or getting access to view something via SC?

Sorry, I'm not sure what "SC" refers to here?  It sounds like on-campus or VPN access.  While most items in DataSpace are only accessible over the VPN or on-campus, there are some that are completely open.  Users do not log into DataSpace to access materials.

> Online Access: accessible online to authorized users of the Princeton University computing network (as described above). again, this sounds like Princeton Net ID/access via SC.

I think this is VPN or on-campus access as well.

> Walk-in Access Only: as you note above. If they want their desktop to hang with Figgy, we had to have Steph A. and her team come in to help with that as well for Special Collections. Has Steph been over there to see what the setup is like?

I'm meeting with Christa today and should be able to get back to you with more info on this!


* The summary in the abo
Thank you, @kelynch ! SC is "Special Collections" in this context and I have edited my original comment accordingly, spelling out the acronym. sorry about that!! :)

comments.body: Given that the rails `time_zone` configuration seems to be partially about converting the zone back and forth during database updates / access, and we won't be storing this with active record, it might be good to be more explicit.
Oh my understanding was the rails time zone defines what the TZ Time.current and such returns, and the AR config was what did the database stuff.

Hm, I see what you mean. That configuration just makes Rails convert anything it sees to the configured time zone? Would this have implications for our other values? It doesn't seem to be a field-specific configuration.

Looks like the global configuration will be disruptive of other date values, including years entered for other properties. We'd have to do a data migration or something? Here's a sample test run showing the way years would behave https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/pulibrary/figgy/4628/workflows/05cc6aaf-7070-4bae-becb-a5552c34ac1b/jobs/39488
What do you think we should do?
